+0106.11d8d6 (1982). Correction

Date: 2024, May 7

File: Zakhodyakin1982d.pgn

Study no. 207 (Table 1 in beatochess-01)

In Zakhodyakins original study, 1. Rh4 is not a cook due to 1. Nd5. However, there are cooks on move 4 and 5. The same-material correction has two main lines, depending on Blacks choice on move 5.

=0340.20h2h5 (1982). Correction

Date: 2024, May 7

File: Zakhodyakin1982g.pgn

Study no. 217 (Table 1 in beatochess-01)

The first two moves can be interchanged. This can easily be fixed by placing the black bishop on a different square, allowing the refutation Rg7 after 1. Kh1. The correction adds a bit more spice, at the cost of an additional white pawn.

GBR: =0340.20h2h5 FEN: 6r1/1B4b1/2P3P1/7k/8/8/7K/8 w - - 0 1

Shakhmaty v SSSR/9. (U1) Neuenschwander=B beatochess 07/05/2024. 1. c7! (1. Kh1 minor dual 1 Be5 2. c7) 1 Be5+ 2. Kh1 (2. Kh3? Bxc7 3. Bd5 Re8! 4. g7 Re3+ 5. Kg2 Rg3+) 2 Bxc7 3. Bd5! Rg7 (3 Rxg6 4. Bf7) 4. Bf7! 1/2-1/2.

GBR: =0340.30h2h5 FEN: 5br1/1B6/2P3P1/3P3k/8/8/7K/8 w - - 0 1

correction: Neuenschwander=B beatochess 07/05/2024. 1. c7! (1. Kh1? Rg7) 1 Bd6+ 2. Kh1! (2. Kh3? Bxc7 3. d6 Bxd6 4. Bd5 Re8 5. g7 Re3+ 6. Kg2 Rg3+) 2 Bxc7 3. d6! Bxd6 4. Bd5! Rg7 5. Bf7 1/2-1/2.

In Weeninks original study, various first moves lead to a win. The key of the study is to keep the black king on the last rank (or the h-file), which is shown in the correction.

Weenink +0130.11c2g4 (1919). Correction (twin)

Date: 2024, May 17

File: Weenink1919a.pgn

Study no. 20 (Table 1 in beatochess-01)

The cooks on move 2 are serious. On the other hand, the cook on move 11 is less relevant. The position after 4. h7 Bh8 can be won in various move orders, but the idea is the same (zugzwang). The study can be saved by getting rid of the cook on move 2 and stop the main line when the white pawn reaches h7.

The version is a twin study which has considerable more content than Weeninks original study.

GBR: +0130.11c2g4 FEN: 8/8/5b2/8/6kP/8/1pK4R/8 w - - 0 1

Rd2! cook GH/EB ) 2 Kg5 3. h6 Kg6 4. h7 Bh8 5. Kb1 Kg5 6. Rh2! Kg6 7. Ka2 Kf7 (7 Kg5 8. Rxb2) 8. Rg2 Bg7 9. Kb1 Kf8 10. Rf2+ Ke7 11. Rh2 (11. Rxb2! cook JU ) 11 Bh8 12. Rg2 Kf7 13. Rg8 1-0.
